<section type="title">
<heading>
An Introduction to the English Tongue						
						
PART I						
						
The ALPHABET of LETTERS				
</heading>		
						
English		Roman		Italian		The Names of
														the Letters
a	A	      a A	    a	A	      ay
b	B	      b	B	    b	B	      bee
c	C	      c	C	    c	C	      see
d	D	      d	D	    d	D	      dee
e	E	      e	E	    e	E	      e
f	F	      f	F	    f	F	      eff
g	G	      g	G	    g	G	      jee
h	H	      h	H	    h	H	      aitsh
i	I	      i	I	    i	I	      i
j		      j	J	    j	J	      jay, or jee
k	K				k	K			k	K				cay
l	L				l	L			l	L				ell
m	M				m	M			m	M				em
n	N				n	N			n	N				en
o	O				o	O			o	O				o
p	P				p	P			p	P				pee
q	Q				q	Q			q	Q				cu
r r	R			r R			r R				ar
s s S			s s S		s s S			ess
t	T				t	T			t	T				tee
v					v V			v V				vee, or ev
u	U				u	U			u	U				yu
w	W				w	W			w	W				double yu
x	X				x	X			x	X				eks
y	Y				y	Y			y	Y				wi
z	Z				z	Z			z	Z				zad, or zed.
						
</page>						
<page no="2">					
						
The Vowels.						
a e i o u, and y, when it follows a Consonant.			
						
The Consonants.						
b c d f g h j k l m n p q r s t v w x y z.						
						
Double Letters						
ct si fl sl ff sh si ss st ffi ssi ffl &aelig; &oelig; &amp;. 						

<heading>
Of Syllables.						
</heading>

<heading>	
TABLE I.

Words of Two Syllables, having Two Conso&shy;
nants of the same sort in the Middle, that

are to be parted in the Spelling of them,
accented on the First Syllable.
</heading>

<wordgroup1 type="a" object="A"><alpha>A</alpha> 

<wordentry type="h"><form lang="en" lexeme="abbot(n)">Ab-bot
</form><xpln></xpln></wordentry>

</form><xpln></xpln></wordentry>  

<wordentry type="h"><form lang="en" lexeme="accent(n)">ac-cent
</form><xpln></xpln></wordentry>  

<wordentry type="h"><form lang="en" lexeme="adder(n)">ad-der
</form><xpln></xpln></wordentry>  

<wordentry type="h"><form lang="en" lexeme="addle(v)">ad-dle
</form><xpln></xpln></wordentry>  

<wordentry type="h"><form lang="en" lexeme="alley(n)">al-ley
</form><xpln></xpln></wordentry>  

<wordentry type="h"><form lang="en" lexeme="alum(n)">al-lom
